$$ \varepsilon \left(\omega \right)=1-\frac{n{e}^2}{\varepsilon_0m{\omega}^2} $$
\end{document}Where n is the density of electrons in the cloud, e and m are the charge and the effective mass of a single of electron, ϵ0 is the dielectric function of vacuum, and ω is the frequency of the incoming light wave. It is customary to define a useful quantity called plasma frequency or plasmon frequency ωp in terms of the following group of constants:ωp=ne2ε0m\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
